Exactly. The pressure washer isn’t the product. The reason is the product.

People don’t wake up thinking, “I wish my trash can were cleaner.” They wake up thinking, “I don’t want my garage to smell,” “Why are there so many flies?” or “My HOA keeps complaining.”

You have to connect the trash can to things they already care about.

Position the trash can as the dirtiest thing they own.

Most people sanitize their kitchen counters, wash their cars, mop their floors, and bathe their pets.

Then they wheel a container that’s been sitting in rotting food, meat juices, diapers, pet waste, and bacteria back into the garage—where they walk past it every day.

“You clean everything that comes into your home. Why ignore the one thing designed to hold your family’s waste?”

