Brand positioning

Don’t be a pressure washing company.

Be the company that helps neighborhoods feel fresher, healthier, and better cared for.

You’re selling sanitation as a subscription, much like lawn care sells curb appeal as a subscription.

A few tagline ideas

* Your Trash Leaves. The Smell Should Too.
* Fresh Can. Fresh Home.
* The Cleanest Thing About Trash Day.
* Because Your Garage Deserves Better.
* We Clean What Everyone Else Avoids.
* A Cleaner Can Changes Everything Around It.
* Neighborhoods Feel Better When They’re Cleaner.
* Sanitize the One Thing Everyone Forgets.

The strongest positioning, in my view, is to make the trash can a keystone object. People interact with it every week. It’s next to their home, often in the garage, touched by adults and kids, and exposed to heat, food waste, and pests. Once customers see it as part of their home’s hygiene—not just a plastic bin—they stop thinking they’re paying to wash a can and start thinking they’re maintaining a cleaner living environment. That mental shift is what makes a recurring subscription feel worthwhile.